{{Italic title}}
An '''''idée reçue''''' (pronounced {{IPA-fr|ide rəsy|}}), plural '''idées reçues''', a [[French language|French]] phrase literally meaning a received (accepted) idea, is a generally held opinion or concept.  This term was used by [[Gustave Flaubert]] in his work [[Dictionary of Received Ideas|''Le Dictionnaire des idées reçues'']] to refer to clichés and platitudes, most of which are as insipid as they are banal.

{{DEFAULTSORT:Idee recue}}
